solutions.content:
So this problem is an inclusion exclusion principle problem.

As it turns out this problem can be solved in O(n^2 m^2)  time where n is the length and m is the width of your array.

First you make a DP  of size n x m  where DP[i][j] holds the area of the rectangle starting at coordinate (0,0) and ending at coordinate (i,j)

Really this is all the information you need to calculate any rectangle in your matrix

Say we wish to find the area of the rectangle with upper left hand coordinate  (x1, y1) and lower right hand coordinate (x2,y2).

Of course x1<=x2  and y1<=y2

Obviously this box is inside DP[x2][y2]  so what we do next is slice off everything that is not inside our box

You can cut Box DP[x2][y2] into four pieces to get your rectangle with corners (x1,y1) , (x2,y2)

Namely it is as follows DP[x2][y2] - DP[x1-1][y2] - DP[x2][y1-1] + DP[x1-1][y1-1]

We cut out the rectangles DP[x2][y1-1] and DP[x1-1][y2] BUT we should note we cut out the rectangle 
DP[x1-1][y1-1] one too many times so we add it back in.

So in effect you can do this trick and run over all quadruplets (x1,y1)  (x2,y2)

Of course as was said earlier this is O(n^2 m^2)  time constraints.

The Code is Below:      Thank You!   =]

```
class Solution {
public:
    int maxSumSubmatrix(vector<vector<int>>& M, int k) {


        int n=M.size(), m=M[0].size();
        int DP[n][m];
        memset(DP,0,sizeof(DP));

        DP[0][0]=M[0][0];

        for(int i=1;i<m;i++) DP[0][i]=DP[0][i-1] + M[0][i];
        for(int i=1;i<n;i++) DP[i][0]=DP[i-1][0] + M[i][0];

        for(int i=1;i<n;i++)
            for(int j=1;j<m;j++)
            {
                DP[i][j]=DP[i-1][j]+DP[i][j-1]-DP[i-1][j-1] + M[i][j];
            }

        int ret=INT_MIN, cur;

        int M1, M2, M3, M4;

        for(int x1=0;x1<n;x1++)
            for(int x2=x1;x2<n;x2++)
                for(int y1=0;y1<m;y1++)
                    for(int y2=y1;y2<m;y2++)
                    {
                        M1=0; M2=0; M3=0; M4=0;

                        if(x1>0&&y1>0) M1=DP[x1-1][y1-1];
                        if(x1>0) M2=DP[x1-1][y2];
                        if(y1>0) M3=DP[x2][y1-1];

                        M4=DP[x2][y2];

                         cur=M4-M3-M2+M1;

                         if(cur<=k) ret=max(ret,cur);


                    } 
        return(ret);

    }
};
```

