**Solution 2 (Accepted)**: Simply use 2 pointers `i, j` to iterate through each character `ci, cj` of both strings one by one:
- If `ci == 'X' or cj == 'X'`, increment `i` or `j`
- If `ci != cj`, return `false`
- Else, we will have `ci == cj`, at this step, need to check:
	- If `ci == 'L'`, then we must have `i >= j`, otherwise return `false`
	- If `ci == 'R'`, then we must have `j >= i`, otherwise return `false`

Keep looping to the end of both strings and return `true` at the end of the function.
```java
class Solution {
    public boolean canTransform(String start, String end) {
        if (start.length() != end.length()) return false;
        int n = start.length();
        int i = 0, j = 0;
        while (i < n && j < n) {
            while (i < n && start.charAt(i) == 'X') i++;
            while (j < n && end.charAt(j) == 'X') j++;
            if (i == n || j == n) break;
            char s = start.charAt(i);
            char e = end.charAt(j);
            if (s != e) return false;
            if (s == 'L' && i < j) return false;
            if (s == 'R' && i > j) return false;
            i++;
            j++;
        }
        if (i < n) {
            if (start.charAt(i) != 'X') return false;
            i++;
        }
        if (j < n) {
            if (end.charAt(j) != 'X') return false;
            j++;
        }
        return true;
    }
}
