**Observations**

Lets take an example to understand solution:
1. XXXXXXL
We can replace 'XL' with XXXXXLX. Again doing this we can obtain XXXXLXX. Which shows we can move L in left. 
Note: We are able to move L in left as long as there is no R in left side of L.

2. On a similar note we can say R can be moved to right until we have L following R.

**Conclusion**

a. L can not cross R and R cannot cross L i.e. Order of LR in original and final string should be same.
b. R in final string can be at position >= what it was before in original string. It cannot go in left.
c. L in final string can be at position <= what is was before in original string. It cannot go in right.

