solutions.content:
The move is as follows:

1. X can go through R to move to the left
RRRX. -> XRRR

2. X can go through L to move to the right
XLLL -> LLLX

Now go from left to right, have counter to save number of 'X' in end minus number of 'X' in start
```
count = #'X' in end - #'X' in start
```

There could be two scenarios:

         count > 0 means there's an X in start need to move left -> it must go through 'R' in start, not an 'L'
                 i
         start:  R R X
         end  :  X R R

         count < 0 means there's an X in start need to move right -> it must go through 'L' in start, not an 'R'
                 i
         start:  X L L
         end  :  L L X

```
class Solution {
    public boolean canTransform(String start, String end) {
        int n = start.length();

        //check if R and L count match
        String s1 = start.replace("X", "");
        String s2 = end.replace("X", "");
        if (!s1.equals(s2)) {
            return false;
        }

        // count: go from left to right. Number of X in end - Number of X in start
        int count = 0; 
        while(i < n) { 
			// need to move right through 'L', but there's an 'R'
		    if (count < 0 && start.charAt(i) == 'R') {
                return false;
            }
            if (end.charAt(i) == 'X') {
                count++;
            }
            if (start.charAt(i) == 'X') {
                count--;
            }
			// need to move left through 'R', but there's an 'L'
            if (count > 0 && start.charAt(i) == 'L') {
                return false;
            }            
            i++;
        }
        return true;
    }
}
```

