I thought it's a bit funny it was categorized as "brainteaser", why don't they put it under "String"?

Several observations:
1. `L` can be moved all the way to the left with the help of `X`
2. `R` can be moved all the way to the right with the help of `X`
3. `L` and `R` can not switch positions under any circumstances

```java
class Solution {
    public boolean canTransform(String start, String end) {
        if (start.length() != end.length()) return false;
        char[] chars1 = start.toCharArray(), chars2 = end.toCharArray();
        int p1 = 0, p2 = 0, count = 0;
        while (p1 < chars1.length || p2 < chars2.length) {
            while (p1 < chars1.length && chars1[p1] == 'X') {
                count++;
                p1++;
            }
            while (p2 < chars2.length && chars2[p2] == 'X') {
                count--;
                p2++;
            }
            if (p1 == chars1.length || p2 == chars2.length) break;
            if (chars1[p1] != chars2[p2]) return false;
            if (chars1[p1] == 'L' && p1 < p2) return false;
            if (chars1[p1] == 'R' && p1 > p2) return false;
            p1++;
            p2++;
        }
        return count == 0;
    }
}
```

