solutions.content:
#### Idea
'L' can only move to the left. This means that 'L' should appear in `end` string before in `start`.
XL -> LX : OK
LX -> XL :  Not OK

'R' can only move to the right. This means that 'R' should appear in `start` string before in `end`.
RX -> XR : OK
XR -> RX: Not OK

'L' and 'R' cannot cross each other. This means that all 'L's found in `end` must be cleared before finding 'R' in `start` and vice versa.
XX..RL -> XX..L..R : Not possible

In the end, all 'L's and 'R's must be cleared.

```
class Solution {
    public boolean canTransform(String start, String end) {
        if (start.length() != end.length()) return false;

        int len = start.length(), lCnt = 0, rCnt = 0;

        for (int i = 0; i < len; i++) {
            char sc = start.charAt(i);
            char ec = end.charAt(i);
            if (ec == 'L') {
                if (rCnt > 0) return false; // L, R need to cross each other so fail.
                else lCnt++;
            } 
            if (sc == 'L') {
                if (lCnt == 0) return false; // L appears in start before appearing in end
                else lCnt--;
            }
            if (sc == 'R') {
                if (lCnt > 0) return false; // L, R need to cross each other so fail.
                else rCnt++;
            }
            if (ec == 'R') {
                if (rCnt == 0) return false; // R appears in end before appearing in start
                else rCnt--;
            }
        }
        return lCnt == 0 && rCnt == 0; // all L and R are cleared.
    }
}
```
TIme Complexity: O(n) - a simple loop through the given strings.
Space Complexity: O(1) - only L and R counts are used.

