solutions.content:
Intuition:

Scan the two strings, at each index compare the character at the index from either string, depending on the comparison we perform diferent actions.

Some observations:
```
Firstly, replacing XL with LX basically means moving the character L to the left by one position, 

Similary replacing RX with XR means moving the character X to the left by one position. 

Notice that there is no way of moving a character R to the LEFT (can be moved to the right, but that does not help us with what we are trying to achieve).
```

Let's say for the current index ```i```:

The main idea is that whenever we found a mismatch, we will need to check if there is a way of finding the target character on the ```start``` string from the remaining substr (i.e ```start[i+1:n-1]```), and moving it along to the current index ```i```.

Based on the observations above, if the target character is ```L```, then the substr mentioned above needs to be ```XXXX...XL```, similarly if the target character is ```X```, then it needs to be ```RRRR....RX```. If the target character is ```R```, there is nothing we can do.

`Algorithm:`
1. compare the characters from both strings at every each position.
2. The two charactesr are ame: All good, continue on for both strings.
3. The two charactesr are different:
* 	target character is ```R```. cannot do anything, return false.
* 	target character is ```L```. look for substr ```XXXX...XL``` from string ```start```, move along ```L``` to the current position, then move on to the next position for both strings.
* 	target character is ```X```. look for substr ```RRRR...RX``` from string ```start```, move along ```X``` to the current position, then move on to the next position for both strings.


```
class Solution {
public:
    bool canTransform(string start, string end) {
        int n=start.size();
        int px=0,pr=0;
        for(int i=0,j=0; i<n && j<n; j++)
        {
            if(start[i]==end[j])
            {
                i++;
            }
            else if(end[j]=='R') 
            {
                return false;
            }
            else
            {
                char c2=end[j];
                char c1=(c2=='L')?'X':'R';

                int k=max(i,(c2=='L')?px:pr);
                while(k<n && start[k]==c1) k++;
                if(k==i || k==n || start[k]!=c2) return false;

                start[k]=c1;                
                start[i]=c2;
                if(c2=='L') px=k;
                else pr=k;
                i++;
            }
        }

        return true;
    }
};
```

