(2-1)For any 'L',  its position in "start" must to the right of that in "end", b/c 'L' can only move to left. 

(2-2)For any 'R', then its position in "start" must to the left of that in "end", b/c 'R' can only move to right.

# Approach
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->
Two pointers. One pass. If any of the above conditions are violated, return false. Otherwise, rethen true.
# Complexity
